<h2>Best HVAC Systems for Orlando Climate</h2>
<p>For Orlando's hot-humid climate, high-efficiency air conditioning systems with SEER ratings of 16 or higher are essential. The most effective systems combine superior cooling capacity with enhanced moisture removal features. Variable-speed air handlers and two-stage compressors excel in Orlando's conditions by running longer at lower speeds, providing better dehumidification while maintaining consistent temperatures. Heat pumps are particularly well-suited for Orlando, offering year-round efficiency with cooling in summer and gentle heating during the brief winter months. Systems with humidity control features can maintain indoor humidity levels between 40-50%, preventing mold growth and improving comfort. Given Orlando's 8-9 month cooling season, investing in 17+ SEER systems typically provides excellent returns through reduced electricity costs with Duke Energy's 11.6¬¢/kWh rates.</p>

